nce%2C%20GOBankingRates%20noted%20the%20annual%20price%20of%20groceries%20in%20Hawaii%20was%20%245%2C339%2C%20while%20annual%20housing%20costs%20were%20over%20%2435%2C800.%20Utilities%20were%20also%20by%20far%20the%20highest%20at%20%246%2C913%20each%20year.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMassachusetts%2C%20with%20annual%20expenditures%20averaging%20%2485%2C600%2C%20was%20the%20second-most%20expensive%20state%20for%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftop-ten-countries-for-a-comfortable-retirement-2023-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ecomfortable%20retirement%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20at%20%241.6%20million%20for%2025%20years%20and%20%241.92%20million%20for%2030%20years.%20Housing%20costs%20were%20over%20%2426%2C500%20a%20year%2C%20while%20utilities%20were%20%245%2C866%20annually.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ECalifornia%20and%20New%20York%20ranked%20third%20and%20fourth%2C%20respectively.%20California's%20minimum%20for%2025%20years%20of%20comfortable%20retirement%20was%20%241.43%20million%2C%20well%20above%20New%20York's%20at%20%241.29%20million.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThough%20not%20brought%20up%20in%20cost%20of%20living%20debates%20to%20the%20same%20extent%20as%20California%20or%20Florida%2C%20Alaska%20was%20fifth%20on%20the%20list%20with%20a%20nearly%20identical%20retirement%20minimum%20as%20New%20York.%20Alaska%20had%20the%20highest%20annual%20cost%20of%20groceries%20of%20any%20state%20at%20%245%2C814%2C%20as%20well%20as%20the%20most%20expensive%20annual%20healthcare%20costs%20at%20%2411%2C227.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EConversely%2C%20West%20Virginia%2C%20Mississippi%2C%20and%20Oklahoma%20were%20the%20three%20most%20affordable%20states%20for%20a%20comfortable%20retirement.%20Retirees%20needed%20%24692%2C300%20for%20a%2025-year%20retirement%20in%20West%20Virginia%20and%20%24714%2C000%20in%20Mississippi.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAmericans%20are%20conflicted%20over%20how%20much%20to%20save%20for%20retirement.%20A%20survey%20from%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fpressroom.aboutschwab.com%2Fpress-releases%2Fpress-release%2F2023%2FSchwab-Study-Workers-Continue-to-Prioritize-401K-Saving-Amid-Anxiety-About-Inflation-and-Market-Volatility%2Fdefault.aspx%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EAugust%202023%20by%20Charles%20Schwab%3C%2Fa%3E%20found%20that%20US%20workers%20believed%20they%20should%20save%20up%20%241.8%20million%20to%20retire%20comfortably%20%E2%80%94%20which%20just%20over%20a%20third%20said%20they%20could%20reach.%20Another%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.schroders.com%2Fen-us%2Fus%2Finstitutional%2Fmedia-center%2Fjust-10-of-non-retired-americans-will-wait-until-70-to-take-maximum-social-security-benefits%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EAugust%20survey%20by%20Schroders%3C%2Fa%3E%20determined%20that%20adults%20expect%20to%20need%20about%20%245%2C000%20a%20month%20for%20a%20comfortable%20retirement%2C%20or%20about%20%241.5%20million%20over%2025%20years.%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.aarp.org%2Fretirement%2Fplanning-for-retirement%2Finfo-2020%2Fhow-much-money-do-you-need-to-retire.html%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EAARP%20estimates%3C%2Fa%3E%20Americans%20need%20to%20save%20enough%20to%20replace%20about%2080%25%20of%20their%20pre-retirement%20income%2C%20which%20comes%20to%20%242%20million%20for%20a%2025-year%20retirement%20for%20a%20worker%20making%20%24100%2C000%20a%20year.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMany%20Americans%20fear%20they%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fboomers-not-enough-retirement-savings-gen-z-millennials-eldercare-2024-1%23%3A~%3Atext%3DDespite%2520holding%2520more%2520than%2520half%2C%252427%252C180%2520for%2520a%2520single%2520person.%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ewon't%20have%20nearly%20enough%3C%2Fa%3E%20for%20retirement%2C%20citing%20inflation%20for%20food%20and%20housing%20costs.%20Many%20younger%20Americans%20are%20starting%20retirement%20savings%20accounts%20earlier%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fgen-z-most-financially-savvy-generation-retirement-saving-investing-2023-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Emore%20aggressively%3C%2Fa%3E%20than%20their%20parents.%20Some%20are%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fretirement-saving-henrys-401k-paycheck-to-paycheck-high-earners-millennials-2023-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Esaving%20too%20much%20for%20retirement%2C%3C%2Fa%3E%20such%20that%20they're%20sacrificing%20spending%20on%20what%20matters%20to%20them.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmost-expensive-states-to-retire-in-hawaii-massachusetts-california-million-2024-1%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1704971341000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F659ed2ddec62ab5daf8253d5%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmost-expensive-states-to-retire-in-hawaii-massachusetts-california-million-2024-1%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Hawaii%20is%20the%20most%20expensive%20state%20for%20a%20comfortable%20retirement%20at%20over%20%242%20million%20for%2025%20years%2C%20followed%20by%20Massachusetts%2C%20California%2C%20and%20New%20York.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22nsheidlower%40insider.com%20(Noah%20Sheidlower)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A10%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmost-expensive-states-to-retire-in-hawaii-massachusetts-california-million-2024-1%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Your%20tax%20dollars%20are%20getting%20spent%20on%20weight-loss%20drugs%20like%20Ozempic%2C%20and%20the%20total%20is%20adding%20up%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222121%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Ozempic%20pen%20with%20stethoscope%20and%20tape%20measure%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6571e9600ec98e92f74d1c80%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221414%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3E%3Cp%3ECarolina%20Rudah%2FGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3EAs%20demand%20for%20weight%20loss%20drugs%20grows%2C%20so%20too%20do%20the%20costs%20for%20some%20insurance%20plans.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EThat%20might%20be%20weighing%20on%20taxpayers%2C%20who%20fund%20Medicaid%20and%20state%20health%20plans.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3ENorth%20Carolina%20State%20Treasurer%20Dale%20Folwell%20said%20the%20state's%20health%20plan%20is%C2%A0%26quot%3Bunder%20financial%20siege.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Ozempic%20craze%20is%20continuing%20to%20cascade%20across%20America%20%E2%80%94%20and%20local%20governments%20are%20worried%20taxpayers%20can't%20afford%20to%20fund%20it%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Emuch%20longer.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOver%20the%20past%20year%2C%20demand%20for%20weight-loss%20drugs%20like%20Ozempic%2C%20Wegovy%2C%20and%20similar%20types%20of%20medications%20known%20as%20GLP-1s%20have%20surged%20as%20Americans%20fawned%20over%20the%20drugs'%20quick%20results%20to%20shed%20some%20pounds.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAt%20a%20cost%20of%20sometimes%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fozempic-wegovy-weight-loss-drugs-doctors-patients-broken-healthcare-system-2023-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Eover%20%241%2C000%20a%20month%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20some%20people%20are%20not%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.wsj.com%2Fhealth%2Fhealthcare%2Fozempic-mounjaro-weight-loss-drug-cost-32fc3555%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Epaying%20for%20these%20drugs%20out%20of%20pocket%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Instead%2C%20they%20rely%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhow-much-ozempic-costs-with-insurance-2023-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Etheir%20health%20insurance%20plans%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20or%2C%20in%20some%20cases%2C%20state-funded%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fjamanetwork.com%2Fjournals%2Fjama-health-forum%2Ffullarticle%2F2789704%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3EMedicaid%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20cover%20them.%20Some%20companies%20are%20refusing%20to%20do%20so%2C%20and%20the%20cost%20is%20beginning%20to%20weigh%20on%20state%20and%20local%20governments%20that%20fund%20employee%20plans.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.bloomberg.com%2Fnews%2Farticles%2F2024-01-05%2Fozempic-s-cost-weight-loss-drugs-will-be-billed-to-us-taxpayers%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Ea%20Bloomberg%20analysis%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20of%202022%20data%2C%20Medicaid%20spent%20%247.9%20billion%20on%20GLP-1s%20in%202022%20pre-rebates%20from%20manufacturers%2C%20and%20reimbursements%20are%20expected%20to%20rise%20this%20year%20as%20more%20people%20seek%20out%20the%20drugs.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EConnecticut%20was%20quick%20to%20experience%20the%20impact%20of%20weight%20loss%20drugs%20on%20its%20economy%20last%20year.%20Politico%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.politico.com%2Fnews%2F2023%2F11%2F15%2Fweight-loss-drugs-00127203%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Ereported%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20November%20that%20the%20state's%20employee%20health%20plan%20was%20set%20to%20spend%20%2430%20million%20on%20drugs%20like%20Ozempic%20and%20Wegovy.%20Comptroller%20Sean%20Scanlon%20told%20BI%20that%20that%20was%20up%20from%20%248%20million%20in%202020.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20drugs%20were%20a%20small%20but%20quickly%20growing%20percentage%20of%20what%20the%20plan%20was%20doing%20for%20pharmacy%2C%20accounting%20for%203%25%20of%20their%20pharmacy%20trend%2C%20according%20to%20Scanlon.%20Whenever%20trend%20lines%20are%20going%20in%20the%20wrong%20direction%2C%20Scanlon%20said%2C%20it's%20going%20to%20come%20back%20to%20the%20taxpayers%20in%20time.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20try%20to%20find%20solutions%20that%20meet%20both%20of%20my%20statutory%20obligations%20to%20be%20the%20watchdog%2C%20but%20also%20to%20run%20a%20plan%20that's%20good%20and%20going%20to%20actually%20give%20people%20healthcare%20that's%20good%2C%20because%20I%20just%20fundamentally%20believe%20that%20that%20is%20a%20good%20thing%20for%20us%20as%20a%20society%2C%26quot%3B%20Scanlon%20told%20BI.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EScanlon's%20office%20set%20out%20to%20reevaluate%20and%20find%20a%20potential%20solution%20that%20would%20ensure%20people%20could%20still%20access%20the%20drugs%2C%20but%20in%20a%20way%20that%20requires%20buy-in.%20Connecticut%20began%20testing%20out%20a%20method%20to%20offer%20those%20seeking%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Eweight%20loss%20drugs%20access%20to%20a%20program%20with%20online%20tools%20for%20weight%20management.%20They%20can%20also%20then%20meet%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Ewith%20providers%20to%20discuss%20any%20medication%20that%20might%20be%20necessary%2C%20as%20Politico%20reported.%20The%20program%20is%20intended%2C%20in%20part%2C%20to%20ensure%20that%20recipients%20are%20also%20making%20lifestyle%20changes%20that%20will%20ensure%20the%20drugs%20are%20effective%20over%20time.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20trend%20of%20people%20seeking%20these%20out%20has%20continued%20to%20get%20bigger%2C%20and%20that%20was%20anticipated.%20We%20were%20not%20trying%20to%20do%20this%20to%20stifle%20demand%2C%26quot%3B%20Scanlon%20said.%20%26quot%3BWe%20were%20trying%20to%20give%20people%20access%20to%20drugs%20so%20that%20the%20drug%20can%20actually%20work.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMeanwhile%2C%20other%20areas%20and%20plans%20are%20simply%20just%20pulling%20back%20on%20coverage.%20In%20North%20Carolina%2C%20the%20State%20Health%20Plan%20has%20put%20a%20moratorium%20on%20new%20users%20of%20GLP-1%20drugs%20for%20weight%20loss.%20It%20was%20in%20reaction%20to%20their%20plan%20%26quot%3Bbeing%20under%20financial%20siege%2C%26quot%3B%20according%20to%20North%20Carolina%20Treasurer%20Dale%20Folwell.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe're%20seeing%20exponential%20increases%20in%20the%20amount%20of%20money%20that%20we're%20having%20to%20pay%20on%20this%2C%26quot%3B%20Folwell%20told%20BI.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFolwell%20said%20that%20continuing%20to%20cover%20the%20drugs%20would%20have%20potentially%20resulted%20in%20premiums%20doubling%20on%20individual%20coverage.%20Currently%2C%20the%20drug%20is%20costing%20them%20%2422%20a%20member%2C%20he%20said%20%E2%80%94%20while%20cancer%20medication%20comes%20in%20at%20%2416%20a%20member%2C%20and%20chemotherapy%20is%20%2417%20a%20member.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOriginally%2C%20the%20Plan%20was%20projected%20to%20spend%20over%20%24170%20million%20on%20Wegovy%20and%20Saxenda%20in%202024.%20With%20the%20new%20moratorium%2C%20it'll%20come%20in%20closer%20to%20%24130%20million%20this%20year.%20If%20the%20state's%20legislature%20did%20subsequently%20provide%20more%20funding%20for%20the%20State%20Health%20Plan%2C%20it%20could%20theoretically%20result%20in%20more%20taxes%20to%20offset%20that%20cost%2C%20should%20the%20General%20Assembly%20decide%20that%20would%20be%20the%20pay-for.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFolwell%20has%20previously%20called%20on%20manufacturer%20Novo%20Nordisk%20to%20price%20the%20drugs%20%26quot%3Bfairly%2C%26quot%3B%20according%20to%20a%20press%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nctreasurer.com%2Fnews%2Fpress-releases%2F2023%2F10%2F24%2Ftreasurer-folwell-calls-novo-nordisk-lower-unfair-cost-weight-loss-drugs%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3E%20release%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20saying%20that%20it%20%26quot%3Bdefies%20logic%26quot%3B%20that%20Novo%20Nordisk%20can%20sell%20its%20product%20for%20%24296%20in%20the%20Netherlands%20and%20for%20over%20%24800%20a%20month%20in%20the%20United%20States.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20believe%20as%20the%20chair%20of%20the%20state%20health%20plan%20board%20and%20the%20state%20treasurer%2C%20state%20employees%20deserve%20to%20have%20the%20opportunity%20to%20buy%20this%20drug%20at%20the%20same%20price%20as%20the%20company%20that%20manufactures%20it%20sells%20it%20to%20citizens%20of%20its%20own%20country%2C%26quot%3B%20Folwell%20told%20BI.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENovo%20Nordisk%20said%20in%20a%20statement%20to%20BI%20that%20it%20%26quot%3Bbelieves%20the%20best%20way%20to%20stem%20the%20significant%20cost%20burden%20of%20obesity%20on%20our%20country%20is%20to%20ensure%20all%20Americans%20living%20with%20obesity%20have%20basic%20insurance%20coverage%20for%20the%20full%20continuum%20of%20care.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThere%20is%20variability%20in%20US%20employer%20coverage%20and%20reimbursement%20for%20anti-obesity%20medications%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20statement%20said.%20%26quot%3BCurrently%2C%20more%20than%2050%20million%20Americans%20living%20with%20obesity%20have%20access%20to%20this%20therapy%20class%2C%20which%20represents%20a%20trend%20of%20expanded%20coverage%20in%20government%20healthcare%20and%20commercial%20plans.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBusiness%20Insider's%20Shelby%20Livingston%20has%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Femployers-stop-covering-weight-loss-drugs-due-cost-price-2023-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Epreviously%20reported%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20on%20the%20negative%20economic%20impacts%20these%20drugs%20are%20having%20on%20companies'%20and%20governments'%20budgets.%20Since%20the%20drugs%20can%20cost%20over%20%241%2C000%20a%20month%20%E2%80%94%20and%20since%20they're%20not%20cures%20%E2%80%94%20many%20people%20have%20to%20take%20them%20for%20life%2C%20which%20can%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwill-company-health-insurance-pay-weight-loss-drugs-ozempic-wegovy-2023-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Ecome%20at%20a%20huge%20cost%20to%20employers%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Some%20employers%20are%20cutting%20the%20drugs%20out%20of%20their%20insurance%20coverage%20completely%20due%20to%20ballooning%20costs%2C%20as%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.wsj.com%2Fhealth%2Fhealthcare%2Femployers-cut-off-access-to-weight-loss-drugs-for-workers-cb277a44%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3EWall%20Street%20Journal%20previously%20reported%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnd%20while%20the%20major%20manufacturers%20of%20the%20drugs%2C%20Eli%20Lilly%20and%20Novo%20Nordisk%2C%20have%20said%20the%20drug%20will%20pay%20off%20over%20time%20because%20it'll%20save%20money%20on%20expensive%20procedures%2C%20there%20is%20no%20clear%20data%20to%20prove%20that'll%20be%20the%20case%20%E2%80%94%20and%20states%20are%20working%20in%20the%20meantime%20to%20bring%20the%20costs%20down.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20instance%2C%20the%20University%20of%20Texas%20System%20said%20over%20the%20summer%20that%20it%20was%20moving%20away%20from%20covering%20weight%20loss%20drugs%20%E2%80%94%20since%20continuing%20to%20cover%20the%20drugs%20would%20add%20%2473%20million%20annually%20to%20prescription%20plans%2C%20forcing%20premiums%20to%20rise%20by%202.5%25%20to%203%25.%20The%20costs%20of%20the%20drugs%20had%20risen%20from%20%241.5%20million%20per%20month%20to%20%245%20million%20per%20month%20over%20just%2018%20months%2C%20with%20over%203%2C000%20plan%20members%20receiving%20the%20drugs%2C%20the%20UT%20System%20said%20in%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.utsystem.edu%2Fsites%2Fdefault%2Ffiles%2Fdocuments%2Fpublication%2F2023%2Fannual-enrollment-resource-guide-employees%2F202324aenewsletteremp.pdf%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Ebenefits%20newsletter%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BCost%20analysis%20on%20these%20medications%20indicates%20they%20are%20currently%20the%20costliest%20prescription%20drugs%20paid%20for%20by%20the%20plan%20on%20an%20annual%20basis%2C%20even%20more%20costly%20than%20medications%20for%20complex%20conditions%20like%20cancer%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20benefits%20newsletter%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20states%20battle%20the%20costs%20of%20GLP-1s%2C%20it%20doesn't%20look%20like%20demand%20will%20settle%20down%20anytime%20soon%20%E2%80%94%20and%20it%20could%20change%20the%20way%20the%20broader%20economy%20is%20shaped.%20Business%20Insider%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fsemaglutide-wegovy-ozempic-weight-loss-healthcare-airlines-economy-productivity-2023-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Epreviously%20reported%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20while%20people%20are%20spending%20less%20on%20food%20as%20they%20turn%20to%20the%20drugs%2C%20the%20money%20is%20just%20being%20reallocated%20to%20wellness%20and%20lifestyle%20products.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BConsumers%20are%20looking%20for%20better-for-you%20products%2C%26quot%3B%20Nik%20Modi%2C%20a%20managing%20director%20at%20RBC%20Capital%20Markets%20who%20focuses%20on%20consumer%20goods%2C%20previously%20told%20BI.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fozempic-weight-loss-drugs-insurance-medicaid-taxpayer-dollars-2024-1%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1704971341000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F659efe01ec62ab5daf82727f%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fozempic-weight-loss-drugs-insurance-medicaid-taxpayer-dollars-2024-1%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20growing%20demand%20for%20weight%20loss%20drugs%20is%20leaving%20some%20taxpayer-funded%20health%20plans%20cash-strapped.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22insider%40insider.com%20(Juliana%20Kaplan%2CAyelet%20Sheffey)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A9%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fozempic-weight-loss-drugs-insurance-medicaid-taxpayer-dollars-2024-1%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22TCS%20Q3FY24%20results%3A%20Net%20profit%20up%202%25%20to%20Rs%2011%2C058%20cr%2C%20revenue%20up%204%25%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1704971280000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fbsmedia.business-standard.com%2F_media%2Fbs%2Fimg%2Farticle%2F2023-04%2F19%2Ffull%2F1681892675-9443.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.business-standard.com%2Fcompanies%2Fresults