uts-powell-inflation-2023-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ecutting%20interest%20rates%20would%20stimulate%20the%20economy%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20making%20it%20easier%20for%20businesses%20to%20get%20loans%2C%20invest%2C%20and%20hire.%20Rather%20than%20a%20nonpartisan%20response%20to%20the%20shifting%20sands%20of%20the%20economy%2C%20the%20theory%20claims%2C%20the%20reason%20for%20the%20coming%20rate%20cuts%20is%20that%20the%20Fed%20and%20its%20chair%2C%20Jerome%20Powell%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ffederal-reserve-chairman-jerome-powell-trump-resignation-2019-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ehate%20former%20President%20Donald%20Trump%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20want%20to%20keep%20Biden%20in%20office.%20It's%20best%20to%20cut%20rates%20to%20boost%20the%20economy%2C%20improving%20voters'%20opinion%20of%20Biden%20heading%20into%20the%202024%20elections%2C%20the%20thinking%20goes.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ERight%20now%2C%20most%20of%20the%20commentary%20saying%20the%20Fed%20is%20trying%20to%20boost%20Biden%20is%20coming%20from%20former%20Trump%20administration%20officials%20or%20other%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftwitter.com%2Fj_fishback%2Fstatus%2F1745080315918397555%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3ERepublican-leaning%20commentators%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20but%20that%20doesn't%20mean%20Democrats%20are%20immune%20from%20trying%20to%20politicize%20the%20Fed.%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthehill.com%2Fbusiness%2F4379295-democrat-fed-should-cut-interest-rates-or-be-most-responsible-for-trumps-return%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3EDemocratic%20Rep.%20Ro%20Khanna%20said%20the%20Fed%20needed%20to%20cut%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20interest%20rates%20or%20Powell%20%26quot%3Bmay%20be%20the%20person%20most%20responsible%20for%20the%20possible%20return%20of%20Trump.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ERegardless%20of%20which%20party%20is%20haranguing%20the%20Fed%2C%20it's%20important%20for%20Powell%20and%20the%20rest%20of%20the%20central%20bank%20not%20to%20look%20political.%20An%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftrump-federal-reserve-interest-rate-attacks-echo-nixon-disaster-2018-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eapolitical%20independent%20central%20bank%3C%2Fa%3E%20is%20a%20good%20thing%20for%20everyone%20because%20monetary%20policymaking%20free%20from%20political%20pressures%20will%20tend%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftrump-federal-reserve-interest-rate-attacks-echo-nixon-disaster-2018-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eresult%20in%20a%20more%20stable%20economy%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Setting%20interest%20rates%20should%20be%20about%20weighing%20costs%20and%20benefits%20for%20everyone%2C%20not%20engineering%20outcomes%20for%20a%20favored%20constituency.%20When%20people%20(usually%20those%20with%20a%20vested%20political%20interest)%20try%20to%20accuse%20the%20Fed%20of%20being%20biased%2C%20it%20erodes%20confidence.%20Don't%20fall%20for%20these%20lies%3A%20The%20accusation%20that%20the%20Fed%20is%20being%20political%20or%20trying%20to%20boost%20Biden's%20reelection%20chances%20has%20a%20few%20glaring%20problems.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3ERate%20cuts%2C%20they%20just%20make%20sense%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20first%20piece%20of%20the%20%26quot%3BFed%20is%20trying%20to%20boost%20Biden%26quot%3B%20conspiracy%20theory%20is%20the%20idea%20that%20the%20central%20bank%20is%20suddenly%20reversing%20course%20on%20its%20inflation%20fight%2C%20as%20if%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Finterest-rates-when-will-federal-reserve-cut-bank-of-america-2023-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EPowell%20flipped%20on%20a%20dime%3C%2Fa%3E%20as%20the%20election%20came%20into%20view.%20There's%20an%20easy%20way%20to%20check%20this%20idea%3A%20Every%20quarter%2C%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fdid-fed-pause-raise-interest-rate-hikes-september-inflation-recession-2023-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EFed%20releases%20its%20Summary%20of%20Economic%20Projections%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20which%20breaks%20down%20the%20Fed%20governors'%20and%20board%20members'%20projections%20for%20GDP%2C%20inflation%2C%20unemployment%2C%20and%20the%20appropriate%20federal%20funds%20interest%20rate.%20These%20forecasts%20are%20conditional%2C%20not%20a%20set-in-stone%20promise%20of%20what%20the%20Fed%20will%20do%2C%20but%20they%20provide%20a%20useful%20picture%20of%20the%20various%20members'%20thinking%20about%20economic%20conditions%20at%20the%20time.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20most%20recent%20summary%2C%20released%20in%20December%2C%20the%20Fed%20signaled%20that%20it%20planned%20to%20cut%20rates%20from%205.5%25%20to%204.5%25%20by%20the%20end%20of%202024.%20This%20was%20a%20change%20from%20the%20previous%20forecast%2C%20released%20in%20September%2C%20that%20estimated%20a%202024%20year-end%20rate%20of%205%25.%20The%20change%20was%20seen%20as%20a%20sign%20from%20the%20%26quot%3BFed%20is%20political%26quot%3B%20camp%20that%20Powell%20et%20al.%20were%20laying%20the%20groundwork%20for%20more%20cuts%2C%20thereby%20boosting%20the%20economy%20for%20Biden.%20In%20fact%2C%20December's%204.5%25%20projection%20was%20the%20same%20rate%20projected%20in%20June's%20Summary%20of%20Economic%20Projections%20%E2%80%94%20the%20September%20release%20was%20the%20aberrant%20one.%20Rather%20than%20suddenly%20reversing%20course%2C%20a%20sign%20of%20some%20sort%20of%20political%20motivation%2C%20the%20summary%20has%20consistently%20shown%20that%20the%20Fed%20members%20started%20projecting%202024%20rate%20cuts%20in%20June%202022%2C%20roughly%201%20%C2%BD%20years%20ago.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESecond%2C%20there's%20nothing%20special%20about%20recent%20revisions%20to%20the%20Fed's%20interest-rate%20projections.%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fdream-economic-scenario-inflation-job-market-unemployment-growth-federal-reserve-2023-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EInflation%20is%20slowing%20more%20rapidly%3C%2Fa%3E%20than%20expected%2C%20and%20the%20US%20job%20market%2C%20while%20solid%2C%20has%20shown%20early%20signs%20of%20shakiness%2C%20so%20it%20stands%20to%20reason%20that%20the%20Fed%20would%20react%20accordingly.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20the%20unemployment%20rate%20remains%20low%2C%20it%20has%20ticked%20up%20somewhat%20from%20its%20recent%20bottom%2C%20and%20other%20labor-market%20indicators%2C%20such%20as%20the%20hiring%20and%20quits%20rates%2C%20have%20weakened%20in%20recent%20months.%20Given%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2F2024-outlook-us-economy-stock-market-jobs-inflation-interest-rates-2023-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Esigns%20we've%20seen%20from%20the%20economy%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20the%20Fed's%20adjustments%20to%20its%20forecast%20are%20pretty%20standard%20according%20to%20what's%20known%20as%20the%20Taylor%20rule.%20The%20rule%20says%20that%20as%20projections%20for%20inflation%20decrease%2C%20the%20Fed's%20forecast%20for%20its%20key%20interest%20rate%20should%20also%20go%20down.%20In%20the%20December%20Summary%20of%20Economic%20Projections%2C%20the%20Fed%20revised%20its%20projection%20for%20year-end%202024%20core%20personal%20consumption%20expenditures%20inflation%20%E2%80%94%20the%20Fed's%20favorite%20gauge%20for%20inflation%20%E2%80%94%20downward%20by%20a%20total%20of%200.7%20points.%20According%20to%20the%20Taylor%20rule%2C%20the%20Fed%20should%20have%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fstock-market-outlook-disinflation-federal-reserve-rate-cuts-goldman-sachs-2023-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Elowered%20its%20projections%20for%20the%20federal%20funds%20interest%20rates%20as%20well%3C%2Fa%3E%20%E2%80%94%20and%20it%20did.%20A%20rule%20of%20thumb%20would%20be%20to%20cut%20interest%20rates%20by%20half%20the%20total%20revision%20to%20core%20personal%20consumption%20expenditures%2C%20so%20another%200.35%20points%20off%20the%20federal%20funds%20rate%2C%20which%20is%20exactly%20what%20it%20did.%20Rather%20than%20some%20political%20conspiracy%2C%20the%20rate-cut%20forecast%20is%20just%20rules-based%20common%20sense.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20third%20reason%20the%20political-Fed%20idea%20makes%20no%20sense%20is%20that%20history%20suggests%20Powell%20and%20the%20other%20members%20are%20operating%20well%20within%20precedent.%20Our%20nearby%20table%20shows%20where%20unemployment%20and%20core%20inflation%20were%20at%20the%20time%20of%20the%20Fed's%20first%20interest%20rate%20cuts%20in%20the%20past.%20The%20unemployment%20rate%20was%2C%20on%20average%2C%20up%200.3%20percentage%20points%20from%20its%20low%2C%20while%20core%20personal-consumption-expenditures%20inflation%20was%20running%202.5%25%20at%20an%20annual%20rate%20in%20the%20three%20months%20leading%20up%20to%20the%20first%20cut.%20Where%20are%20we%20now%3F%20The%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Funemployment-rate-job-growth-labor-market-wages-december-economic-outlook-2024-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%20headline%20unemployment%20rate%20stands%20at%203.7%25%2C%3C%2Fa%3E%200.3%20points%20above%20its%20prior%2012-month%20low%2C%20while%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhigh-inflation-goods-durables-deflation-groceries-expensive-federal-reserve-cars-2023-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ecore%20PCE%20inflation%20has%20climbed%202.16%25%20at%20an%20annual%20rate%20%3C%2Fa%3Eover%20the%20past%20three%20months.%20That%20means%20core%20inflation%20is%20actually%20running%20somewhat%20below%20where%20it%20normally%20is%20when%20the%20Fed%20starts%20cutting.%20There's%20nothing%20abnormal%20about%20these%20cuts.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%20data-script%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20data-styles%3D%5C%22default-width%5C%22%20data-embed-type%3D%5C%22custom%5C%22%20data-type%3D%5C%22embed%5C%22%3E%3Ciframe%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fdatawrapper.dwcdn.net%2F8Kw1D%2F1%2F%5C%22%20title%3D%5C%22Economic%20data%20when%20the%20Fed%20started%20to%20cut%20rates%5C%22%20data-external%3D%5C%221%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22531%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fiframe%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cp%3EAlso%2C%20it's%20not%20as%20if%20the%20Federal%20Reserve%20is%20acting%20alone.%20Several%20global%20central%20banks%20have%20already%20started%20cutting%20policy%20rates%2C%20and%20markets%20indicate%20that%20investors%20are%20already%20anticipating%20more%20rate%20cuts%20from%20the%20G10%20(the%2010%20countries%20that%20represent%20the%20most%20traded%20currencies)%20central%20banks%20in%20the%20coming%20year.%20Are%20all%20these%20central%20banks%20bailing%20out%20politicians%20up%20for%20reelection%3F%20In%20many%20of%20these%20countries%20%E2%80%94%20Canada%2C%20the%20UK%2C%20Australia%2C%20and%20Japan%20%E2%80%94%20there%20are%20no%20national%20elections%20until%202025.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt's%20also%20worth%20noting%20that%20many%20of%20those%20accusing%20the%20Fed%20of%20being%20political%20have%20argued%20that%20there%20are%20%26quot%3Blong%20and%20variable%20lags%26quot%3B%20to%20monetary%20policy%2C%20meaning%20that%20adjustments%20made%20to%20interest%20rates%20today%20will%20be%20felt%20in%20the%20economy%2012%20to%2018%20months%20from%20now.%20If%20that's%20right%2C%20then%20a%20political%20Fed%20should%20have%20already%20cut%20by%20now%20to%20guarantee%20that%20the%20effect%20of%20the%20cuts%20would%20be%20greasing%20the%20economy%20in%20time%20for%20the%20elections%20this%20fall.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFinally%2C%20for%20all%20the%20nonsense%20about%20%26quot%3BBiden%20appointees%2C%26quot%3B%20or%20this%20being%20a%20Fed%20controlled%20by%20Biden%2C%20the%20very%20same%20Fed%20has%20shown%20itself%20to%20be%20apolitical.%20Some%20pushing%20the%20conspiracy%20theory%20point%20to%20an%20op-ed%20written%20by%20Bill%20Dudley%20in%20August%202019%2C%20shortly%20after%20leaving%20his%20post%20as%20the%20head%20of%20the%20New%20York%20Fed.%20In%20it%2C%20Dudley%20wrote%20that%20if%20the%20Fed%20boosted%20the%20economy%20by%20cutting%20rates%2C%20then%20the%20central%20bank%20would%20be%20implicitly%20enabling%20Trump's%20trade%20war%20%E2%80%94%20a%20move%20Dudley%20thought%20would%20be%20seriously%20misguided.%20It%20was%20a%20provocative%20piece%2C%20by%20Dudley's%20own%20admission%2C%20but%20his%20former%20colleagues%20seemed%20to%20ignore%20it%3A%20The%20Fed%20did%20end%20up%20cutting%20rates%20a%20couple%20of%20times.%20Cut%20to%20today%2C%20and%20the%20person%20who%20squeezed%20the%20toothpaste%20out%20of%20the%20tube%2C%20so%20to%20speak%2C%20was%20the%20Fed's%20governor%20Chris%20Waller%2C%20appointed%20by%20Trump.%20He's%20the%20one%20who%20publicly%20laid%20out%20the%20playbook%3A%20They're%20following%20a%20rules-based%20framework%20where%20changes%20in%20the%20rate%20of%20inflation%20translate%20to%20changes%20to%20their%20policy%20rate.%20It's%20also%20worth%20noting%20that%20the%20Fed%20is%20presently%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ffed-chair-jerome-powell-trump-pick-for-yellen-replacement-2017-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eled%20by%20someone%20Trump%20himself%20nominated%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20Powell.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EThe%20real%20reason%20for%20the%20accusations%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20entire%20conspiracy%20theory%20about%20a%20political%20Fed%20is%20weak%20on%20its%20face%20and%20baseless%20on%20its%20merits.%20The%20Fed's%20rationale%20for%20rate%20cuts%20makes%20perfect%20economic%20sense%3A%20Inflation%20is%20falling%20more%20rapidly%20than%20expected%20and%20there%20are%20enough%20signs%20of%20labor-market%20softening%20to%20start%20bringing%20down%20the%20federal%20funds%20rate.%20(There%20are%2C%20of%20course%2C%20reasons%20to%20debate%20whether%20cuts%20come%20with%20risks%20%E2%80%94%20such%20as%20overheating%20the%20economy%20later%20or%20if%20it%20makes%20sense%20to%20look%20at%20realized%20inflation%20over%20expected%20inflation%2C%20but%20that's%20not%20what%20this%20debate%20is%20about.)%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20fact%2C%20those%20accusing%20the%20Fed%20of%20being%20political%20are%20being%20political%20themselves.%20The%20Fed's%20detractors%20want%20the%20economy%20to%20be%20weak%20because%20they%20have%20been%20negative%20about%20the%20economy%2C%20and%20it%20would%20help%20confirm%20their%20economic%20predictions%20or%20boost%20their%20employment%20prospects%20in%20a%20Republican%20administration.%20And%20rapidly%20cooling%20inflation%20makes%20it%20harder%20to%20use%20high%20prices%20as%20a%20political%20cudgel.%20Instead%20of%20accepting%20the%20economic%20reality%20as%20it%20is%2C%20they%20start%20from%20a%20conclusion%20first%20and%20work%20backward.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAt%20any%20rate%2C%20all%20this%20complaining%20about%20the%20Fed's%20actions%20may%20not%20have%20much%20of%20an%20effect%20on%20the%20election's%20outcome%3A%20Conditions%20were%20worse%20leading%20up%20to%20the%20midterm%20elections%20of%202022%2C%20and%20by%20most%20accounts%2C%20Republicans%20were%20unable%20to%20capitalize%20on%20the%20situation.%20What%20makes%20anyone%20so%20sure%20they'll%20fare%20better%20in%202024%20with%20the%20rate%20of%20inflation%20slowing%2C%20interest%20rates%20falling%2C%20and%20stocks%20rising%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThere%20are%20reasons%20to%20be%20critical%20of%20the%20Fed.%20It%20may%20have%20eased%20too%20much%20during%20the%20pandemic.%20They%20may%20have%20been%20too%20slow%20to%20normalize%20policy.%20Those%20mistakes%20at%20least%20can%20be%20justified%20by%20faulty%20analysis%20%E2%80%94%20many%20people%20made%20the%20same%20mistake.%20However%2C%20accusing%20the%20Fed%20of%20being%20political%20is%20a%20different%20type%20of%20critique.%20In%20this%20case%2C%20it%20assumes%20the%20Fed%20has%20a%20political%20preference%2C%20which%20undermines%20confidence%20in%20the%20institution%20itself.%20And%20if%20the%20central%20bank%20loses%20credibility%2C%20no%20matter%20the%20reason%2C%20it%20would%20be%20seriously%20problematic%20for%20the%20US%20economy.%20Given%20that%20fact%2C%20it's%20important%20to%20reject%20baseless%20attacks%20on%20the%20Fed%20and%20recognize%20the%20coming%20rate%20cuts%20for%20what%20they%20are%3A%20an%20attempt%20to%20maintain%20low%20unemployment%20and%20stable%20inflation.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fauthor%2Fneil-dutta%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3E%3Cu%3ENeil%20Dutta%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cem%3E%C2%A0is%20head%20of%20economics%20at%20Renaissance%20Macro%20Research.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fdumb-lie-economy-interest-rates-inflation-federal-reserve-2024-election-2024-1%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1704968881000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F659f013b6979d73718223343%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fdumb-lie-economy-interest-rates-inflation-federal-reserve-2024-election-2024-1%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Conspiracy%20theorists%20have%20set%20their%20sights%20on%20a%20new%20target%3A%20the%20Fed.%20And%20that's%20bad%20news%20for%20the%20US%20economy.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22insider%40insider.com%20(Neil%20Dutta)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A18%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fdumb-lie-economy-interest-rates-inflation-federal-reserve-2024-election-2024-1%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Woman%20Posts%20Sketches%20Of%20Son%2C%20Louis%20Vuitton%20Hires%20Him%20As%20Intern%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cp%3EFrench%20luxury%20brand%20Louis%20Vuitton%20recently%20granted%20a%20teenager%20his%20dream%20internship%20after%20a%20few%20of%20his%20sketches%20went%20viral%20on%20social%20media.%20The%2013-year-old%20boy%2C%20Milan%2C%20drew%20sketches%20of%20shoes%2C%20heels%20and%20clothes%2C%20all%20inspired%20by%20the%20brand%2C%20as%