rl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fm-timesofindia-com.cdn.ampproject.org%2Fc%2Fs%2Fm.timesofindia.com%2Fworld%2Fchina%2Fno-mercy-now-xi-jinping-targets-officials-business-meals-in-anti-graft-fight%2Famp_articleshow%2F106719689.cms%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fm.timesofindia.com%2Fworld%2Fchina%2Fno-mercy-now-xi-jinping-targets-officials-business-meals-in-anti-graft-fight%2Famp_articleshow%2F106719689.cms%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22India%20Endorses%20Call%20for%20Humanitarian%20Ceasefire%20in%20Gaza%20in%20Joint%20Statement%20with%20UAE%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F01%2F11113438%2FGDdfl0zbUAA73pF.jpeg%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ENew%20Delhi%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20India%20appears%20to%20have%20endorsed%20a%20call%20for%20humanitarian%20ceasefire%20in%20Gaza%20in%20a%20joint%20statement%20with%20the%20United%20Arab%20Emirates%20on%20Thursday%2C%20January%2011.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20statement%20came%20after%20the%20visit%20of%20UAE%20President%20Sheikh%20Mohamed%20bin%20Zayed%20Al%20Nahyan%20to%20Gujarat%20from%20January%209-10%2C%20as%20the%20chief%20guest%20of%20the%20Vibrant%20Gujarat%20summit.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20statement%20touches%20upon%20several%20points%20of%20India-UAE%20partnership%2C%20including%20note%20on%20Memorandums%20of%20Understanding%20signed%20by%20the%20two%20heads%20of%20government.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETowards%20the%20end%2C%20it%20noted%20that%20Modi%20and%20Al%20Nahyan%20both%20emphasised%20on%20the%20importance%20of%20multilateralism%20and%20%E2%80%9Ccalled%20for%20collective%20action%20to%20promote%20a%20just%2C%20rules-based%20global%20order.%E2%80%9D%20The%20Indian%20side%2C%20according%20to%20the%20statement%2C%20congratulated%20the%20UAE%20for%20its%20successful%20tenure%20as%20an%20elected%20member%20of%20the%20UN%20Security%20Council%20for%20the%202022-23%20term%2C%20and%20commended%20the%20efforts%20led%20by%20the%20UAE%20in%20the%20UNSC%20%E2%80%93%20including%20the%20adoption%20of%20resolution%202720%20penned%20by%20the%20UAE%20concerning%20the%20humanitarian%20crisis%20in%20Gaza.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThen%20it%20said%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CBoth%20leaders%20reiterated%20the%20need%20to%20unite%20efforts%20to%20immediately%20reach%20a%20humanitarian%20ceasefire%20in%20Gaza%20to%20allow%20safe%2C%20unhindered%2C%20and%20expanded%20humanitarian%20access%20at%20scale.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20is%20a%20rare%20line%20to%20have%20made%20its%20way%20into%20a%20bilateral%20document%20signed%20by%20India.%20India%20has%20so%20far%20not%20mentioned%20the%20%E2%80%9Cceasefire%E2%80%9D%20in%20any%20national%20statements%20made%20at%20the%20UN%20during%20discussions%20on%20voting%20about%20the%20violence%20in%20Gaza.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20supported%20the%20UNGA%20resolution%20in%20December%20that%20called%20for%20an%20immediate%20humanitarian%20ceasefire%2C%20but%20even%20then%2C%20India%E2%80%99s%20explanation%20of%20vote%20had%20not%20referred%20to%20any%20ceasefires.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOn%20January%209%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fdiplomacy%2Fcivilian-deaths-unacceptable-conflict-triggered-by-october-7-attack-india-at-unga%5C%22%3Ewhile%20speaking%20at%20the%20UN%20General%20Assembly%20India%E2%80%99s%20permanent%20representative%20to%20the%20UN%20Ruchira%20Kamboj%3C%2Fa%3E%20said%20that%20the%20ongoing%20conflict%20had%20%E2%80%9Cled%20to%20%5Bthe%5D%20large-scale%20loss%20of%20civilian%20lives%2C%20especially%20women%20and%20children%2C%20and%20has%20resulted%20in%20an%20alarming%20humanitarian%20crisis%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhile%20stating%20that%20the%20scale%20of%20the%20loss%20of%20civilian%20lives%20in%20the%20Israel-Hamas%20war%20is%20%E2%80%9Cunacceptable%E2%80%9D%2C%20India%20also%20asserted%20that%20the%20trigger%20for%20the%20war%20was%20Hamas%E2%80%99s%20terror%20attack%20and%20called%20for%20the%20unconditional%20release%20of%20hostages%20held%20by%20the%20Pa